{"id": "chatcmpl-Dimiupeht7OXSXZMHJ8hk7DGyJEO8", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "stop", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": "{
  "analysis": "Plan format is simple line-based: first line CAP n; then ROOT task lane turn; CHILD parent task lane turn; DROP task (branch removal). Turns are integers when the row becomes ready/arrives. Need to simulate acceptance per turn with bounded per-lane CAP: each turn, for each lane (ordered by name), accept up to CAP ready rows in plan-file order within that lane. Ready rows include those with arrival turn <= current turn and not yet accepted, excluding dropped branches+descendants; child rows do not depend on parent acceptance. Must de-dup repeated logical child entries (flint has duplicate flint-a); accept once. Also cancellation semantics: DROP removes named task and every descendant in child chain, regardless of lane/turn and even if descendant appears before DROP line; also keep them out of accepted trace even if previously accepted? spec: 'keeps cancelled branches and their descendants out of the accepted trace' implies retroactive removal. We'll implement by building full graph first, applying DROP closure, then simulating acceptance on remaining unique tasks. Need compute parent/depth for accepted records for hierarchy; depth: ROOT=0, child depth = parent depth +1 following declared parent chain (even if parent dropped? but dropped nodes removed). We'll write /app/scripts/executor-ctl (python3) and modify run-matrix.sh/run-one.sh to call it. Create /app/output/runtime directory as work (even if unused) and generate per-case ledger/journal paths (probably inside work). We'll choose /app/output/runtime/{case}.ledger.jsonl and .journal.txt and reference them in audit JSON.",
  "plan": "1) Implement python script at /app/scripts/executor-ctl with argparse supporting --case, --out, --work. 2) For each case: parse plan; build nodes with (kind, task, parent, lane, turn, order_index). Build parent map for depth calculation; validate no cycles. Apply drops: compute closure of dropped tasks via parent->children adjacency, mark removed. De-dup by task name (keep earliest plan order for that task); if duplicates differ, still treat same logical task once. 3) Simulate turns from 0..max_turn over remaining tasks: maintain per-lane queue of ready tasks sorted by (turn, order_index) but eligible when turn<=t; each turn, for lanes sorted lexicographically, accept up to CAP tasks not yet accepted. Record acceptance turn=t. 4) Build trace sorted by accepted turn then lane then acceptance sequence within lane for that turn (which naturally follows plan order). 5) Write ledger JSONL and journal txt in trace order. 6) Build audit JSON with cases array in required order and fields: name, ok (finished and no pending), finished (bool), pending (list of pending tasks records?), trace (records), ledger (path), journal (path). Pending should include remaining non-accepted non-dropped tasks if any. finished true when all remaining tasks accepted. 7) Update run-matrix.sh and run-one.sh to call python script. 8) Run run-matrix.sh and verify output exists and is deterministic by running twice and diffing.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "apply_patch<<'PATCH'\n*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: scripts/executor-ctl\n+#!/usr/bin/env python3\n+import argparse\n+import json\n+import os\n+from dataclasses import dataclass\n+from typing import Dict, List, Optional, Set, Tuple\n+\n+\n+CASE_ORDER = [\"amber\", \"cobalt\", \"drake\", \"ember\", \"flint\", \"graphite\"]\n+\n+\n+@dataclass(frozen=True)\n+class Row:\n+    kind: str              # ROOT | CHILD\n+    task: str\n+    parent: Optional[str]  # None for ROOT\n+    lane: str\n+    ready_turn: int\n+    plan_index: int\n+\n+\n+def parse_plan(path: str) -> Tuple[int, List[Row], Set[str]]:\n+    cap: Optional[int] = None\n+    rows: List[Row] = []\n+    drops: Set[str] = set()\n+\n+    with open(path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n+        for idx, raw in enumerate(f):\n+            line = raw.strip()\n+            if not line or line.startswith(\"#\"):\n+                continue\n+            parts = line.split()\n+            if parts[0] == \"CAP\":\n+                if len(parts) != 2:\n+                    raise ValueError(f\"bad CAP line: {line}\")\n+                cap = int(parts[1])\n+                continue\n+            if parts[0] == \"DROP\":\n+                if len(parts) != 2:\n+                    raise ValueError(f\"bad DROP line: {line}\")\n+                drops.add(parts[1])\n+                continue\n+            if parts[0] == \"ROOT\":\n+                if len(parts) != 4:\n+                    raise ValueError(f\"bad ROOT line: {line}\")\n+                _, task, lane, turn_s = parts\n+                rows.append(Row(\"ROOT\", task, None, lane, int(turn_s), idx))\n+                continue\n+            if parts[0] == \"CHILD\":\n+                if len(parts) != 5:\n+                    raise ValueError(f\"bad CHILD line: {line}\")\n+                _, parent, task, lane, turn_s = parts\n+                rows.append(Row(\"CHILD\", task, parent, lane, int(turn_s), idx))\n+                continue\n+        